Core Framework: The core framework provides the foundation for Robot Framework. It's responsible for parsing test data files, interpreting keywords, and managing the overall test execution flow. 

Test Data: Test cases are written in a human-readable tabular format using plain text files. These files contain keywords, arguments, and comments that define the testing steps. 

Libraries: Libraries are reusable modules that provide functionalities for interacting with different applications, databases, operating systems, or external tools. Robot Framework offers a rich set of built-in libraries, and you can also create custom libraries using Python or other languages. 

Task Repository: The task repository stores the actual implementation of keywords defined in libraries. This separation between keyword definitions and implementations enhances modularity and maintainability. 

Reporting: Robot Framework generates comprehensive reports in HTML format after test execution. These reports provide detailed information on test results, logs, and even screenshots (if applicable). 

